Normally I have pretty good food but last night my food was not the best. I ordered for delivery(through Doordash) which was some spicy wings and a Greek salad with shrimp. The wings were good but the shrimp on the salad were so overcooked I couldn't eat some of them. When I called the next morning to tell them about the shrimp I was told that's just how they cook the shrimp and that I would have to call the delivery company.  I don't see why I have to call the delivery company when there wasn't a problem with the delivery but with the actual food. I have never had shrimp that overcooked before. Might be a while before I order again and it definitely won't be something with shrimp.
